&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who/What is Artefact?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Artefact is a next-generation strategy and data consulting firm dedicated to transforming&amp;nbsp;organizations through data and AI. We combine the rigor of top-tier strategy consulting&amp;nbsp;with deep expertise in data, digital, and analytics to help clients achieve tangible&lt;br&gt;business impact.&lt;br&gt;With 1,800+ consultants, data scientists, and engineers across 23 countries, we work&amp;nbsp;with global leaders such as Samsung, L’Oréal, Orange, and Sanofi. Our Zurich office is&amp;nbsp;at the heart of Artefact’s growth, advising clients on their most pressing strategic&amp;nbsp;challenges — from AI strategy and governance to digital transformation roadmaps and&amp;nbsp;new business model design.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;As a AI Manager in Pharma &amp;amp; Life Science in our Zurich office, you will be at the intersection of strategy consulting and data/AI innovation. You will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategy Development: &lt;/strong&gt;Work with client leadership teams (specifically in the Pharma &amp;amp; Life Sciences sector) to address high-stakes questions: How can AI reshape our business model? How should we govern and organize for data? Which strategic programs deliver the most impact?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Structured Problem-Solving:&lt;/strong&gt; Break down complex challenges into clear,&amp;nbsp;actionable recommendations, using frameworks and methodologies rooted in&amp;nbsp;classic strategy consulting, enriched by Artefact’s data and AI expertise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Delivery:&lt;/strong&gt; Support engagements end-to-end, from hypothesis framing&amp;nbsp;and market/competitor analysis to client workshops, governance design, and&amp;nbsp;implementation roadmaps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Engagement:&lt;/strong&gt; Collaborate closely with C-level stakeholders and business&amp;nbsp;unit leaders. You’ll build trusted relationships, communicate recommendations&amp;nbsp;with clarity, and ensure strategic alignment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Knowledge &amp;amp; Practice Building:&lt;/strong&gt; Contribute to the growth of Artefact’s Zurich&amp;nbsp;office by shaping new offerings, creating intellectual capital (frameworks, thought&amp;nbsp;pieces, benchmarks), and participating in business development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Management: &lt;/strong&gt;Lead, mentor, and foster collaboration within hybrid project teams, ensuring high-quality delivery and team growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidate Profile&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an ambitious, analytically minded talent who is passionate about&amp;nbsp;leveraging data and AI to solve business problems. The ideal candidate meets several&amp;nbsp;of the following qualifications:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education:&lt;/strong&gt; Bachelor’s and Master’s degree (preferred) in Business,&amp;nbsp;Engineering, Computer Science, Economics or a related field. An excellent&amp;nbsp;academic track record is highly valued.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; Approximately 5–8 years of experience in strategy consulting with a mandatory focus on the Pharma &amp;amp; Life Sciences sector and&amp;nbsp;with a proven track record of delivering data, analytics, or AI-driven transformation projects.&lt;/li&gt;
