&lt;p&gt;Artefact is a next-generation strategy and data consulting firm dedicated to transforming organizations through data and AI. We combine the rigor of top-tier strategy consulting with deep expertise in data, digital, and analytics to help clients achieve tangible business impact. With 2,000+ consultants, data scientists, and engineers across 26 countries, we work with global leaders such as Samsung, L’Oréal, Orange, and Sanofi. At our German offices, we are on a rapid growth trajectory, advising leading national and international clients cross-industry on how to unlock the full potential of their data, build scalable data architectures, and implement cutting-edge AI solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Consulting Manager (m/f/d) Data &amp;amp; AI Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;, you will act as a trusted sparring partner to executives, steer complex transformation programs across functions, and drive organizational change at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead AI Transformation Programs:&lt;/strong&gt; Steer end-to-end execution of enterprise-level AI transformations. Identify internal champions, navigate corporate politics, manage structural blockers, and drive measurable user adoption and organizational change.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategy &amp;amp; AI Use Case Scoping:&lt;/strong&gt; Work closely with C-level stakeholders to answer high-stakes questions: How can AI reshape their business models? How should they govern data? You don&#39;t just advise; you help evaluate model choices, discuss data privacy trade-offs, and conceptualize technical feasibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Business Growth:&lt;/strong&gt; Actively drive the growth of our German practice. Take ownership in lead generation and pipeline conversion by engaging prospective clients, shaping proposals, and leading pre-sales and key-account expansion initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thought Leadership &amp;amp; Advocacy:&lt;/strong&gt; Represent Artefact&#39;s AI Transformation perspective externally. Advance our voice in enterprise AI through expert discussions, content creation (e.g. LinkedIn, whitepapers), and opinionated, hands-on perspectives on applied AI trends and real-world adoption pathways.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advance the Practice:&lt;/strong&gt; Evolve our methodologies, tools, and frameworks to keep our offering state-of-the-art. Develop reusable transformation playbooks and bring your strategic consulting or technology expertise into the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Leadership &amp;amp; Mentoring:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as a senior advisor and role model - leading, coaching, and mentoring agile, hybrid project teams (consultants, data scientists, and engineers), fostering a fast-paced, “can-do” culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidate Profile&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At our heart, we define ourselves by a culture of ownership, intellectual curiosity, and cooperation. &lt;strong&gt;We are looking for driven, capable talents who bring strong motivation and curiosity for new challenges.&lt;/strong&gt; You are a true team player, eager to support others while scaling both the company and your own career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; You have approximately 5–8 years of full-time working experience in top-tier management consulting, technology consulting, or strategic corporate in-house roles. A proven track record of successfully leading and delivering data, analytics, or AI-driven transformation projects is essential.&lt;/li&gt;
